benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/catalog/xml - Upload the full catalog as XML

covered: Valid Payload coverage: TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC13, TC24, TC28, TC29, TC30, TC31 demonstrate successful uploads across normal, boundary, encoding, and accessibility scenarios.
Invalid Payload coverage: TC06, TC07, TC08, TC09, TC10, TC18, TC23, TC17 demonstrate handling of missing/invalid/malformed payloads and dangerous content.
Duplicate Submission coverage: TC25 confirms handling of duplicate catalog versions.
Large Payload coverage: TC12 validates system behavior with very large XML payloads.
Validation coverage: includes header validation (TC06, TC07), minimal payload (TC13) and boundary/format validation (TC30, TC28, TC29).
Server Error Handling coverage: TC16 validates 503 service unavailability in backend down scenarios.
Authorization coverage: TC14 validates response for missing/invalid authentication.
Performance coverage: TC19 and TC20 cover load and concurrency performance.
Regression coverage: TC21 and TC22 verify known bug regression and backward compatibility.
Edge-case/robustness coverage: TC11 (extra headers) and TC26 (additional URL parameters) and TC27 (whitespace handling) contribute to robustness.
Security coverage: TC17 tests handling of dangerous content (XXE/script injection).
gaps: Rate limiting/throttling: Not explicitly tested for POST requests.
Caching behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) for POST responses.
Explicit content-type acceptance: No dedicated test ensuring valid Content-Type (e.g., application/xml) is accepted (only negative test for application/json is present).
Internal server error coverage beyond 503: No tests simulating 500 errors (DB/service failure).
recommendations: Add rate-limiting tests for POST (e.g., bursts and 429 responses).
Add caching behavior tests for POST responses if applicable.
Add explicit test for valid Content-Type acceptance (e.g., application/xml).
Add 500 Internal Server Error test scenarios (DB/service failure).
Expand security tests for XML parsing (XXE and other parser vulnerabilities).
Add idempotency test for repeated identical uploads (409 or 201 semantics).
Add tests for network resilience beyond TC15 (e.g., intermittent connectivity).
Enhance performance testing with more realistic user loads and throughput metrics.
Extend regression coverage to include more known bug scenarios and cross-version compatibility.
Verify correctness and content of the Location header with created resource URL.
